(July 25, 1961)

In decisions Nos. 1-20 the court is as follows: Present — Bergan, P. J., Gibson, Herlihy, Reynolds and Taylor, JJ.

In the matter of the Claim of Mary Celia, Respondent, v. Elks Club, Inc., et al., Appellants. Workmen’s Compensation Board, Respondent.

Appeal dismissed without costs, unless appellants shall file and serve record, brief and note of issue on or before August 7, 1961 and be ready for argument at the term to commence September 6,1961, in which event the motion is denied.
